article.headline: Tulane 72, Grambling St. 37
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- Asim McQueen scored 14 points on 6 of 9 shooting to lead Tulane to a 72-37 win over Grambling State on Monday night. Kris Richard added 12 points and six rebounds for the Green Wave (6-6). Johnny Mayhane had 10 points, and Kevin Sims dished out seven assists. The Green Wave finished with 24 team assists, and shot 46.7 percent from the field (28-for-60). The Tigers (2-9) were paced by Ibrahim Kpaka, who scored 14. Andrew Prestley added six points and seven rebounds. Grambling State has now lost five straight games. The Tigers shot 30.8 percent from the field (12-for-39), including only 7.7 percent from 3-point range (1-for-13). Tulane outrebounded Grambling State 36-30.
